                            <comment id="11761" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Fri, 10 Dec 2004 22:27:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Indeed, this is currently not possible in a straightforward fashion. We&apos;re planning to add such support to Spring 1.2, possibly as &quot;type&quot; attribute on the &amp;lt;value&amp;gt; tag.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12610" author="cnelson" created="Sat, 19 Mar 2005 03:35:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like this issue (&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-761&quot; title=&quot;Nested Property Editor / Transformer for Collections&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-761&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-761&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) might also be a duplicate.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My apologies... -Christian&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12681" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Wed, 23 Mar 2005 00:36:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve added an optional &quot;type&quot; attribute to the &amp;lt;value&amp;gt; tag, specifying the exact type to convert to before passing the value on. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is also available programmatically, through specifying a TypedStringValue instance as value in a bean definition.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
